abstract.p:
A coating composition comprising a film forming binder of





a. an acrylic polymer having pendant groups that are reactive with isocyanate moieties and having a glass transition temperature (Tg) of 10 to 80°C.;

b. a polytrimethylene ether diol having a Mn (number average molecular weight) of 500 to 5,000; and

c. an organic polyisocyanate crosslinking agent;

wherein the coating composition contains pigments and cures at ambient temperatures or elevated temperatures and forms a coating that is sandable and when used in combination with a top coat, for example, a colored base coat and clear coat or a pigmented mono-coat forms a chip resistant multi-layer coating useful for refinishing or repairing automotive and truck bodies and parts.

description.p:
A coating composition comprising a film-forming binder of





a. an acrylic polymer having pendant groups that are reactive with isocyanate moieties and having a glass transition temperature (Tg) of 10 to 80° C.;

b. a polytrimethylene ether diol having a Mn (number average molecular weight) of 500 to 5,000; and

c. an organic polyisocyanate crosslinking agent;

wherein the coating composition contains pigments and cures at ambient temperatures or elevated temperatures and forms a coating that is sandable and when used in combination with a top coat, for example, a colored base-coat and clear-coat or a pigmented mono-coat, forms a chip resistant multi-layer coating useful for refinishing or repairing automotive and truck bodies and parts.
